actor Client as Browser/client
participant Router as Axum router matching
participant Trace as TraceLayer
participant SetReq as SetRequestIdLayer
participant PropReq as PropagateRequestIdLayer
participant Cors as CorsLayer
participant Compress as CompressionLayer
participant SecHeaders as security_headers middleware
participant Timeout as TimeoutLayer 30s
participant BodyLimit as DefaultBodyLimit on tenant stack
participant AuthMW as auth_middleware
participant TenantMW as tenant_middleware
participant Handler as Handler/extractor
participant Service as Service/helper
participant Pg as PostgreSQL
participant Redis as Redis
participant Fs as Filesystem/uploads
participant ErrorMap as AppError/HTTP status mapping

Note over Router,Timeout: For matched routes, Axum selects the route service, then the Tower stack runs effectively as Trace, SetRequestId, PropagateRequestId, CORS, Compression, security headers, Timeout, then route-stack middleware.
Note over BodyLimit,TenantMW: Tenant routes have a configured body limit and tenant middleware. The limit is configured on the tenant stack and enforced when body extractors read request bodies.

rect rgb(238, 247, 255)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 1 - public health/readiness request
    Client->>Router: GET /health or /ready
    Router->>Trace: matched public system route
    Trace->>SetReq: enter traced request
    SetReq->>PropReq: generate x-request-id if absent
    PropReq->>Cors: propagate x-request-id on response
    Cors->>Compress: apply configured CORS policy
    Compress->>SecHeaders: response compression wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: add security headers after inner response
    Timeout->>Handler: run health/readiness handler
    alt GET /ready
        Handler->>Pg: SELECT 1 readiness probe
        Handler->>Redis: Redis connection and PING
    else GET /health
        Handler-->>Timeout: liveness JSON
    end
    Handler-->>Client: JSON response or AppError mapped status
end

rect rgb(238, 255, 242)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 2 - public login request
    Client->>Router: POST /api/auth/login with JSON body and client IP/connect info
    Router->>Trace: matched auth::public_router route
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: credentialed CORS allowed for configured origin
    Cors->>Compress: response compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies
    Timeout->>Handler: login handler reads JSON body
    Handler->>Service: security::client_ip and require_login_allowed
    Service->>Pg: failed-login tracking query
    Handler->>Pg: load user and refresh-token rows
    Handler->>Service: password::verify_password and jwt::issue_access_token
    Handler->>Pg: insert refresh token record
    Handler-->>Client: JSON auth response plus Set-Cookie zinhar_refresh_token HttpOnly SameSite=Lax
end

rect rgb(250, 248, 255)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 3 - auth-only request
    Client->>Router: GET /api/auth/me or /api/plugins with Authorization: Bearer token
    Router->>Trace: matched protected router route
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: CORS and credentials
    Cors->>Compress: compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies
    Timeout->>AuthMW: route_layer auth_middleware
    AuthMW->>Service: jwt::verify_access_token
    Service-->>AuthMW: Claims extension
    AuthMW->>Handler: continue with Claims
    Handler->>Service: RBAC helpers where route requires role checks
    Handler->>Pg: direct SQLx reads/writes as needed
    Handler-->>Client: JSON or AppError mapped status
end

rect rgb(255, 252, 238)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 4 - tenant-aware request
    Client->>Router: GET /api/pages with Authorization: Bearer token and X-Organization-Id
    Router->>Trace: matched tenant-protected route
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: CORS allows Authorization, Content-Type, X-Organization-Id
    Cors->>Compress: compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies
    Timeout->>BodyLimit: tenant stack body-limit configuration
    BodyLimit->>TenantMW: tenant_middleware
    TenantMW->>Service: jwt::verify_access_token when Claims absent
    TenantMW->>Pg: load active organization membership
    TenantMW->>Service: rate_limit::check_and_record_request
    Service->>Redis: org/user rate-limit counters
    Service->>Pg: load organization rate-limit settings
    TenantMW->>Service: quota::check_and_record_api_request unless quota-exempt path
    Service->>Pg: usage counter update
    TenantMW-->>Handler: add Claims and TenantContext extensions
    Handler->>Service: RBAC/RLS/workflow/audit helpers as applicable
    Service->>Pg: tenant-scoped SQLx queries
    Handler-->>Client: JSON or AppError mapped status
end

rect rgb(255, 244, 238)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 5 - multipart upload
    Client->>Router: POST /api/media/upload multipart/form-data with Bearer token and X-Organization-Id
    Router->>Trace: matched tenant media route
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: CORS
    Cors->>Compress: compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies
    Timeout->>BodyLimit: configure max upload size plus buffer
    BodyLimit->>TenantMW: tenant auth, rate limit, quota API request
    TenantMW->>Handler: upload_media handler
    Handler->>BodyLimit: Multipart extractor reads body under configured limit
    Handler->>Service: quota::ensure_media_capacity
    Service->>Pg: media quota check
    Handler->>Fs: create upload directories and write original file
    Handler->>Service: media_processing::process_image_variants when image
    Service->>Fs: write generated variants
    Handler->>Pg: insert media and variants metadata
    Handler-->>Client: media JSON or mapped upload error
end

rect rgb(245, 245, 245)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 6 - static upload request
    Client->>Router: GET /uploads/{organization_id}/...
    Router->>Trace: matched ServeDir static service
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: CORS layer still applies
    Cors->>Compress: compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies
    Timeout->>Handler: ServeDir static file service
    Handler->>Fs: read file from upload_dir
    Handler-->>Client: file bytes or static-file error; no auth_middleware or tenant_middleware
end

rect rgb(238, 250, 255)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 7 - WebSocket live preview
    Client->>Router: GET /api/preview/{page_id}?access_token=...&organization_id=...
    Router->>Trace: matched tenant pages preview route
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: CORS layer for upgrade request
    Cors->>Compress: compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies to upgrade request
    Timeout->>BodyLimit: tenant stack body-limit configuration
    BodyLimit->>TenantMW: tenant_middleware
    TenantMW->>Service: jwt::verify_access_token from query token when bearer is absent
    TenantMW->>Pg: load active organization membership from query organization_id
    TenantMW-->>Handler: TenantContext extension
    Handler-->>Client: 101 Switching Protocols
    Handler->>Service: in-memory page preview broadcast channel
    Handler->>Pg: load initial page JSON for tenant
    Service-->>Client: WebSocket preview messages
end

rect rgb(255, 238, 245)
    Note over Client,ErrorMap: Variant 8 - Stripe webhook request
    Client->>Router: POST /api/billing/stripe/webhook with Stripe-Signature and raw body
    Router->>Trace: matched billing::public_router route
    Trace->>SetReq: trace request
    SetReq->>PropReq: request id
    PropReq->>Cors: CORS layer applies, but route is public integration endpoint
    Cors->>Compress: compression wrapper
    Compress->>SecHeaders: security headers wrapper
    SecHeaders->>Timeout: timeout applies
    Timeout->>Handler: stripe_webhook handler reads Bytes body and headers
    Handler->>Service: stripe_billing::handle_webhook verifies signature and idempotency
    Service->>Pg: billing_events, subscriptions, plans, audit logs
    Handler-->>Client: webhook result JSON or AppError mapped status
end

Note over ErrorMap,Client: AppError implements IntoResponse and maps Unauthorized, Forbidden, NotFound, BadRequest, Validation, Conflict, TooManyRequests, ServiceUnavailable, and Internal errors to JSON HTTP responses.
